  "text": "The Morningness-Eveningness-Stability-Scale improved (MESSi; [CITATION_1] was used as an improved measure of morningness-eveningness trait composed by selected items of CSM [CITATION_2] , Caen Chronotype Questionnaire (CCQ; [CITATION_3] and Circadian Energy Scale (CIRENS; [CITATION_4] . Three sub-scales were obtained by exploratory, confirmatory factor analysis and external validity analysis: Morning Affect (MA), which was composed by items 3, 4 and 12 of CSM, item 4 of CCQ and morning level of energy from CIRENS. Eveningness (EV), composed by revised item 13 of CSM (evening reformulated), revised items 2 and 11 of CCQ (evening reformulated), item 5 of CCQ and evening level of energy of CIRENS. Finally, Distinctness (DI) was composed by items 6, 8, 10, 14 and 15 of CCQ.",
